b'' b'if "i forgot" doesn\'t have as much credibility as you\'d like, consider' b'this alternative. somewhere on the hard disk, duplicated a few times,' b'keep a 128-bit random number. when the 128-bit digest of your' b'passphrase is computed, it is xorred with the random number before being' b'used as the key for your hard disk. writing random junk over the random' b'numbers makes the hard disk unreadable by anyone.' b'' b'now, if you were merely to *claim* that you have written random junk' b'over the xor key, no-one would be able to tell whether or not you were' b'telling the truth. this is (a) perjury, and (b) vunerable to' b'rubber-hose cryptography, but otherwise effective.' b'__ b"/\\__/ trust me. i know what i'm doing. \\x/ fold a fish for jesus!" 